joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"9e6e500b061b1f855da56b0658af353ff2fc1e6c86ad1a9a7949cba1c51e9dba","event_uuid":"ebab729e-b4df-488c-91fa-946d714e2896","position":{"commit_sha":"150505e7b7894b374c180db87506104c5891d326","position":"1784263237399519001-ebab729e-b4df-488c-91fa-946d714e2896"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"da960dccbfaa494774233d2e77cd827b564f35c4e7140d24cdfd60793a791a50","event_uuid":"57a1f582-0c20-43a8-bca8-a7c110acce82","position":{"commit_sha":"e49f190d4aaa9f5554bfa29ac201654f607751b1","position":"1784263240041086001-57a1f582-0c20-43a8-bca8-a7c110acce82"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-211_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"e533bbc2-be02-4c77-890b-73fde9abf109","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"PRE-FLIP GATE: FAIL (2026-07-17T01:58:48Z) — FLIP HELD, do not enable enforcement yet.\nValidation window C0=7141adf3c..9484fc29a found 2 unsigned non-SNAPSHOT in-scope events: a STATUS+EDIT (a CLAIM) on task 2ad8-f56e-7bc2-4948, author 594c, from agent session 5c2eef83-9ceb-4320-ad07-f54047bb7399 (harness claude-code_2-1-212_agent) at 2026-07-17T01:53:52Z — a DIFFERENT concurrent Claude agent working this shared store on an OLD pre-0ba4 build (its worktree venv predates the finalize_event fix, so txn.claim_core still writes unsigned).\nThis is the multi-agent reality: several agents share this dogfooding store on MIXED builds. My local (global kickstarted + venv) writers sign; CI reconciler + Gerrit review-bot already signed (own paths); but concurrent agents on old worktree venvs still emit unsigned txn events.\nBLOCKER: the flip is safe ONLY once every concurrent writer runs the post-0ba4 build (527a6e730). Resolution: those agents must rebase their worktrees onto current main + reinstall (the global build auto-updates hourly, so fresh agent invocations are already fixed; the persistent risk is long-lived worktree venvs). RE-RUN the pre-flip validation window; flip only when it reports 0 unsigned non-SNAPSHOT events. The gate correctly prevented breaking a live writer — this is the safety mechanism working as designed.","timestamp":1784253529900336001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"FLIP pushed as Gerrit change 759 (https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/c/rebar/+/759). rebar.toml: require_authenticated=true + enforce_since=8dcef776c3dd9e68935b74b82137e1ffd8f04f10, in one change (2026-07-17T03:11:05Z).\n\nENFORCEMENT IS REAL (demonstrated in isolated temp stores, no shared-store pollution):\n- Post-boundary UNSIGNED event -> 'rebar verify-identity --all --require-authenticated' exits 1 (2 unsigned in scope, enforced). Enforcement is real, not advisory.\n- A store with ONLY pre-boundary unsigned events -> exits 0 (correctly grandfathered).\n- The local WRITE-GATE refuses an unsignable non-exempt write under require_authenticated (proven by test_identity_txn_signing_heldout.py::test_unsignable_transition_is_refused_under_enforcement, landed in 0ba4).\n- The landed regression test test_identity_enforce_since_grandfather.py asserts the same boundary behavior (pre grandfathered / post enforced) via the config/env path.\n\nUNDER-ENFORCEMENT WRITER SURFACES (all sign + verify): local (79da), CI reconcile-bridge (4dc0, event 8b72ddf6), Gerrit review-bot LINK (1a51). CI's Verified gate on change 759 runs verify-identity with require_authenticated=true + the pinned anchor over the whole store — a green Verified is the authoritative confirmation that AC1 holds (all pre-boundary grandfathered, all post-boundary verified) and no writer surface goes red.\n\nROLLBACK (fast-revert): if a writer surface unexpectedly fails post-flip, set [identity] require_authenticated=false in rebar.toml (leave enforce_since pinned) and land it as a single Gerrit change (push gerrit HEAD:refs/for/main, Submit once Verified+1). No data cleanup — the gate returns to advisory immediately. Env override REBAR_IDENTITY_REQUIRE_AUTHENTICATED=0 disables it per-run in the interim.","timestamp":1784257866839286001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"FLIP CI (change 759) RED — Verified -1. LLM-Review +1. CI failure is NOT verify-identity — it is one INTEGRATION test: tests/interfaces/store/test_enrich_drain_prune_concurrency.py::test_enrich_queue_prune_never_drops_concurrent_locked_writes (intended=250 persisted=144 lost=106 swallowed_write_raises=106). Root cause: that test spawns subprocess writers that write SIGNATURE/REVIEW_RESULT events to a fresh store with NO signing configured; under require_authenticated=true the write-gate correctly REFUSES the unsignable writes and the drain swallows the raises -> the concurrency invariant (prune never drops writes) sees them as lost. It is a concurrency test, orthogonal to enforcement, that relied on the OLD default (require_authenticated=false). Fix (part of this flip): the worker _prune_race_worker.py must run enforcement-agnostic (set REBAR_IDENTITY_REQUIRE_AUTHENTICATED=0, like it already sets REBAR_SYNC_PUSH=off). In production the review-bot signs (SSM key) so its writes are not refused. NOT a verify-identity/anchor problem — the anchor grandfathering is fine. Amending the flip change with the test fix + re-pushing.","timestamp":1784259821549991001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"FLIP LANDED — enforcement is LIVE (2026-07-17T04:23:38Z). Gerrit change 759 MERGED as origin/main commit 8bb261c19e933b5705a14c0625e9919e0d53634a (LLM-Review+1, Verified+1). origin/main rebar.toml now: [identity] require_authenticated=true, enforce_since=8dcef776c3dd9e68935b74b82137e1ffd8f04f10. The authenticated-authorship merge-gate is now ENFORCING: any in-scope event whose introducing commit descends from the anchor and is not `verified` fails CI. FINAL pre-flip re-validation immediately before submit: 8 in-scope non-SNAPSHOT events in-window, 0 unsigned (CLEAN). This comment itself is a signed write under live enforcement. All ACs met: pre-flip gate (no active unsigned writer), atomic flip + pinned anchor, enforcement-real (temp-store demo + landed regression test), rollback documented.","timestamp":1784262220470639001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"FORCE_CLOSE: close gate(s) bypassed by user approval — no completion/signature attestation was signed. Reason: \"Flip LANDED: Gerrit change 759 MERGED as origin/main 8bb261c19 (LLM-Review+1, Verified+1). require_authenticated=true + enforce_since=8dcef776 live on main; enforcement is now active. Pre-flip gate clean (0 unsigned non-SNAPSHOT); enforcement-real demonstrated; rollback (set false) documented. Operational/tickets-branch ACs recorded on ticket; closing on the merged+Verified flip.\". Session: e533bbc2-be02-4c77-890b-73fde9abf109.","timestamp":1784262223814047001}],"created_at":1784226857982563001,"creation_channel":"unknown","deps":[{"link_uuid":"6e5a1b7c-201c-42ed-b839-2c7a6d1e3c5f","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"79da-c7e4-8d7c-471d"},{"link_uuid":"352b33b8-9915-4ec8-ab90-c6cf15a62eeb","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"4dc0-d003-c236-45de"},{"link_uuid":"5c5b4b91-3e15-4b3f-ad0f-d003fd6dba50","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"1a51-b170-5168-46d2"},{"link_uuid":"0af97b7e-de09-43fc-b3ae-06d59c0dcf81","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"8d91-5103-ae1b-44a7"},{"link_uuid":"28b292d0-94ce-436e-bb3e-123b2f4952f0","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"0ba4-6a28-7a88-47b2"}],"description":"## Why\n\nEnforcement is the epic's goal; it must land **only after** every writer signs (79da local,\n4dc0 CI, 1a51 Gerrit) and grandfathering is proven (8d91). Flipping early turns every push red\nby construction (bug `27ae-8322-9278-4a7c`): with 0 signed events store-wide today, the gate\nwould reject everything. This is the final, atomic switch — and the **only** change that writes\nboth the flag and `enforce_since`.\n\n**Depends on bug `0ba4-6a28-7a88-47b2` (txn signing).** The transactional write path\n(claim/transition/close, and delete) previously wrote UNSIGNED in-scope STATUS/EDIT/ARCHIVED\nevents (they bypassed the signing seam). 0ba4 centralizes signing in a shared `finalize_event`\nchoke point every write routes through. The flip is unsafe until that fix is **landed AND live\nacross every active writer build** (local auto-updates hourly; CI/Gerrit deploy from `main`) —\notherwise a still-old writer keeps emitting unsigned events that the merge-gate rejects. Hence\nthe pre-flip validation AC below: prove no active process is still writing unsigned non-SNAPSHOT\nevents before flipping.\n\n## What\n\n- In `rebar.toml`, in **one** change, set `[identity] require_authenticated = true` **and**\n  `enforce_since = <the anchor SHA documented by 8d91>` (replacing the current rollout-prep pin\n  `ce3f8bcbe13d37e93a0758f7f73cb3ebeac3b043`). No earlier child modifies `enforce_since`; its\n  value equals the exact anchor SHA from 8d91.\n- **Demonstrate enforcement is real** without polluting the shared store:\n  (i) the **merge-gate** fails on a synthetic post-boundary forged/unsigned in-scope event in an\n  isolated temp store (`rebar verify-identity --all --require-authenticated` exits non-zero) —\n  reusing 8d91's harness; and (ii) the **local write-gate** refuses an unsignable write when the\n  signing key is unset (with `require_authenticated=true`, a non-exempt write with no resolvable\n  signing key is refused, exit non-zero) — proving the flag is live, not advisory.\n- **Confirm each writer surface still passes under enforcement**: a representative signed write\n  on local and CI verifies; the Gerrit-side in-scope writer (the review-bot LINK, per 1a51)\n  verifies. No red pushes on `main`.\n- **Provide a documented fast-revert (rollback) path**: how to revert\n  `identity.require_authenticated` to `false` in a single change if a writer surface unexpectedly\n  fails post-flip.\n\n## Scope\n\nThe single atomic config change (flag + boundary) + under-enforcement verification + a rollback\nprocedure. Depends on 79da, 4dc0, 1a51, 8d91. `file_impact`: `rebar.toml` (the flag +\n`enforce_since`); plus a runbook/rollback note.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] **PRE-FLIP GATE — no active process writes an unsigned non-SNAPSHOT in-scope event.**\n      Before flipping, validate over a window in which EVERY active writer operates — a fresh\n      local session write, a `reconcile-bridge` CI run, a Gerrit review-bot write (its\n      `relates_to` LINK on a work ticket), the **enrich drain**, and the **reconciler** — that\n      no active process is still emitting unsigned in-scope events. Method: capture\n      `C0 = git -C .tickets-tracker rev-parse origin/tickets`; let the writers run (or trigger\n      each); fetch `origin/tickets`; then enumerate every event file introduced in\n      `C0..origin/tickets` and assert **every in-scope event carries `author_sig` EXCEPT\n      `*-SNAPSHOT.json`** — SNAPSHOT is the sole permitted unsigned type (a compaction artifact\n      the merge-gate re-verifies via the snapshot's `authorship_ledger`, not the SNAPSHOT event).\n      Proving commands (both must hold):\n      (a) `rebar verify-identity --all --require-authenticated --since C0` exits 0 (every\n      enforced event since `C0` verifies); and\n      (b) no unsigned non-SNAPSHOT event exists in the window — e.g.\n      `git -C .tickets-tracker diff --name-only --diff-filter=A C0..origin/tickets | grep -E '/[0-9].*\\\\.json$' | grep -v -- '-SNAPSHOT.json'`\n      yields only files whose JSON has a non-empty `author_sig`.\n      This confirms bug `0ba4`'s signing fix is LIVE across every writer build (local/CI/Gerrit,\n      incl. the enrich drain + reconciler) so the flip breaks nothing. Record `C0`, the window,\n      and the per-writer signed events observed. If ANY active process still emits an unsigned\n      non-SNAPSHOT event, DO NOT FLIP — remediate that writer first.\n- [ ] **The flip is atomic and pins the 8d91 anchor.** `identity.require_authenticated = true`\n      **and** `enforce_since = 8dcef776c3dd9e68935b74b82137e1ffd8f04f10` land in **one** change; `enforce_since` is written here\n      for the first time (no earlier child modifies it) and its value **equals the exact anchor\n      SHA documented by 8d91**. Proving command:\n      `python -c \"import rebar._config_schema as c, rebar.config as cfg; k=cfg.load_config('.').identity; import sys; sys.exit(0 if (k.require_authenticated and k.enforce_since=='8dcef776c3dd9e68935b74b82137e1ffd8f04f10') else 1)\"`\n      exits 0 (and `git show HEAD:rebar.toml` contains both on the flip commit).\n- [ ] **Enforcement is real, not advisory.** After the flip, `rebar verify-identity\n      --all --require-authenticated` returns **non-zero** on a new in-scope unsigned/forged event\n      (demonstrated in an isolated temp store via 8d91's harness), and the local write-gate\n      **refuses** an unsignable non-exempt write with the signing key unset. Both exits recorded.\n- [ ] **Under enforcement, every in-scope writer surface passes.** A representative signed write\n      on **local** and **CI** shows `authorship: {signed: >=1}` and verifies (its event uuid is\n      absent from `rebar verify-identity --all --format json`); the **Gerrit-side** writer passes\n      iff 1a51 classified one (it did — the review-bot LINK). Evidence (ticket ids + event uuids)\n      recorded on this ticket. No `main` push goes red.\n- [ ] **A documented rollback path exists.** The runbook records the single fast-revert change\n      (set `identity.require_authenticated = false`, land through Gerrit) to use if a writer\n      surface unexpectedly fails post-flip. [operator-attested] the rollback step is captured in\n      the runbook (recorded as a comment on this ticket with the exact revert diff + procedure).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"rebar.toml","reason":"the identity.require_authenticated flip + enforce_since anchor pin"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","0ba4-6a28-7a88-47b2"],["depends_on","1a51-b170-5168-46d2"],["depends_on","4dc0-d003-c236-45de"],["depends_on","79da-c7e4-8d7c-471d"],["depends_on","8d91-5103-ae1b-44a7"],["parent","dc09-6565-cf85-4aea"]],"parent_id":"dc09-6565-cf85-4aea","parent_status_uuid":"12fc8ba4-3bcc-4706-b26e-40da56709a8c","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"closed","tags":[],"ticket_id":"8d39-85d7-8f34-45e6","ticket_type":"story","title":"Flip identity.require_authenticated=true with pinned enforce_since in one change","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["81d37a0d-bb84-4c69-b4c4-e4e570d17bd5","6e5a1b7c-201c-42ed-b839-2c7a6d1e3c5f","352b33b8-9915-4ec8-ab90-c6cf15a62eeb","5c5b4b91-3e15-4b3f-ad0f-d003fd6dba50","0af97b7e-de09-43fc-b3ae-06d59c0dcf81","a517653f-c059-495c-8caf-be5cf7cb8e4f","f2b1c96d-b452-460e-9b7a-49f5ceda57d8","cd4c6aea-cc92-4d55-8550-681e567b7f1f","f433bbe9-5afd-4584-8ebb-99ebf2bbb259","28b292d0-94ce-436e-bb3e-123b2f4952f0","b32684d7-a113-4aab-bb0e-a31bee0388d4","b6f1753f-6229-4f5b-b740-32c8ed9899fe","3dc9d07e-20e3-4266-9699-ad2d44e4321e","87ef7ce9-a3c2-4963-8e72-05b053e8ed47","35441d84-5082-4a70-91b7-0915142e285f","3883cbf6-4320-4ea9-9981-62ad97b8ac2b","91a39cb4-7d86-41c7-9ba7-cf548ae1b558","3165105e-2f8c-4175-a481-019ddacd55bf","9e0f3e87-ae30-460b-ae78-cbdedef2550f","c209f9d0-4bb4-4a0e-b310-de280c84ae88","fe7bb660-df3f-4862-9926-088451d41599","12fc8ba4-3bcc-4706-b26e-40da56709a8c","457899f8-7967-402c-950b-ecdbfdc21fad","ebab729e-b4df-488c-91fa-946d714e2896","57a1f582-0c20-43a8-bca8-a7c110acce82"]},"env_id":"","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784346746484636001,"uuid":"c981c0ec-91c5-441e-8153-df7bfa15de52"}